
[1]rubellite

   RU'BELLITE, n. [from L. rubeus, red.] A silicious mineral of a red
   color of various shades; the red shorl; siberite. It occurs in
   accumulated groups of a middle or large size, with straight
   tubular-like stria. In a red heat, it becomes snow-white and seems to
   phosphoresce.

   Rubellite is red tourmaline.
